                <p><label type="entry">ZAPATA</label>, a kind of feast or ceremony held in Italy in
                    the courts of certain princes, on St Nicholas’s day. People hide presents in the
                    shoes or slippers of those to whom they would do honour, in such a manner as may
                    surprise them on the morrow when they come to dress. This is done in imitation
                    of the practice of St Nicholas, who used in the night-time to throw purses of
                    money in at the windows to furnish marriage-portions to poor maidens.</p>
            </div>
